      • managePasswordRuleDefn

        org.w3c.dom.Document managePasswordRuleDefn(YFSEnvironment env,
                                            org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                                     throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                            java.rmi.RemoteException
        The managePasswordRuleDefn API is used to create, modify, or delete a Password Rule Definition from the system.

        The default Action for the API is Manage, which will act as Create if the specified Password Rule Definition does not exist and act as Modify if it does. Additionally, Delete can be passed to remove an existing Password Rule Definition.

        Related Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Output XML Output DTD Error XML Error DTD

        User Exits: None

        Events Raised: None

        Audits: None

        Pre Conditions: None

        Post Conditions: None

        Output Template Support: Yes.

        Database Extensibility Support: No

        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.
        inXML - Required. For more information, see the associated input xml files.

        Returns:
        An XML document that contains Password Rule Definition data. For details on the output, refer to the associated output files.

        Throws:
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException - Exception containing error codes in the standard error files.
        java.rmi.RemoteException - Java's default remote exception handler.
